Testament. That these now may properly include the New </div><div class="t me29 x0 he y1223 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Testament is attested by the fact that Peter spoke of those who wrested the </div><div class="t m7fe x0 he y1cbf ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">writings of Paul, as they do &quot;the other Scriptures,&quot; to their own destruction. </div><div class="t m27c x0 he y1dc7 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">See 2 Peter 3:16. </div><div class="t m1347 x11 he y1ec6 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;The Bible points to God as its author; yet it was written by human hands; </div><div class="t m75b x0 he y13db ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and in the varied style of its different books it presents the characteristics of </div><div class="t m616 x0 he y1f73 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the several writers. The truths revealed are all &apos;given by inspiration of God&apos; </div><div class="t m8b2 xb7 he yd49 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(2 Tim. 3:16) ; yet they are expressed in the words of men. The Infinite One </div><div class="t m9d7 x0 he y11eb ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">by His Holy Spirit has shed light into the minds and hearts of His servants. </div><div class="t m1f2 x0 he y1faa ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">He has given dreams and visions, symbols and figures; and those to whom </div><div class="t mcff x0 he y1cea ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the truth was thus revealed, have themselves embodied the thought in human </div><div class="t ma9 x0 he yf0d ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">language. </div><div class="t m53c x11 he y1f3f ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;The Ten Commandments were spoken by God Himself, and were written </div><div class="t macf xb7 he y1eb6 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">by His own hand. They are of divine, and not of human composition. But the </div><div class="t m9da x43 h2f y12e3 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">[ 3 ] </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
